# Ganak — rules for Cursor (and any AI agent working in this editor)

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root FIRST and follow it exactly. It is the canonical
conventions file for every agent (Claude, Codex, Cursor). This file just restates
the non-negotiables so Cursor's AI can't miss them.

## Non-negotiable rules
1. **ONE writer on `src/kundli-app.tsx` at a time.** Never edit that file while
   another agent (Claude Code, Codex) is also editing it. If unsure, ask the owner.
   Parallel work should be research/writing into NEW files under `plans/`.
2. **Run the validation gates after any structural edit** and paste the passing
   output — never claim "done" without it:
   ```
   export PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:$PATH"
   node validation/parse-check.js src/kundli-app.tsx   # syntax, orphans, storage ban
   node validation/prashna-parity.js src/kundli-app.tsx
   node validation/prashna-calc.js
   node validation/muhurat-anchors.cjs
   node validation/content-dates.cjs                   # festival/day-part anchors
   ```
3. **No `localStorage` / `sessionStorage`** — banned. UI prefs go in the URL query.
4. **Content is Hindu observances only** (Buddha Purnima excepted). Religious
   content (festival dates, vrat vidhis) must be SOURCED (cite Drik + a second
   source or a named text) and owner-verified — never invented.
5. **Bilingual** (English + Hindi) for all user-facing text.

## How to run the app
Dev server: `npm run dev` (Node is at /opt/homebrew/bin). Node/npm not on PATH by
default — prefix with `export PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:$PATH"`.

## Where things are
- App: `src/kundli-app.tsx` (single ~6,000-line React file).
- Plans / backlog / research: `plans/`.
- Validation gates: `validation/`.
